"{\"uid\": \"nbcsports.com-olympics-news-aryna-sabalenka-paris-olympics-2024-tennis\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Two-time Australian Open champion Aryna Sabalenka said she will not play the Paris Olympics due to scheduling and her health.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 125, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 34, \"end\": 49, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aryna_Sabalenka\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aryna Sabalenka\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aryna_Sabalenka\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aryna_Sabalenka\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am not going to play Olympics because of all the rules from WTA with mandatory tournaments and have to sacrifice something, and unfortunately, I have to sacrifice the Olympics,\\\" she said Monday.\", \"from\": 127, \"to\": 324, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"At this stage of my career, especially with all the struggles I have been struggling with the last months, I feel like I need to take care of my health.\", \"from\": 325, \"to\": 478, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's too much for the scheduling.\", \"from\": 479, \"to\": 512, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's just too much.\", \"from\": 513, \"to\": 532, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I made the decision to take care of my health.\\\"\", \"from\": 533, \"to\": 580, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The WTA Tour announced last Junethat \\\"new player entry rules will ensure a consistent presence of the top athletes\\\" at premium events, such as 1000-level tournaments, which are one level below the four Grand Slams.\", \"from\": 582, \"to\": 796, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Olympic tennis competition runs from July 27 to Aug. 4.\", \"from\": 798, \"to\": 863, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The two weeks after that, a pair of 1000-level WTA tournaments are scheduled in Toronto and Mason, Ohio.\", \"from\": 864, \"to\": 968, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 944, \"end\": 951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toronto\", \"score\": 0.9994338124114466, \"rank\": 0.0005618139741066017, \"text\": \"Toronto\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toronto\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toronto\"}, {\"begin\": 956, \"end\": 967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lindner_Family_Tennis_Center\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.368422185266923e-19, \"text\": \"Mason, Ohio\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lindner_Family_Tennis_Center\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lindner_Family_Tennis_Center\"}, {\"begin\": 956, \"end\": 967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lindner_Family_Tennis_Center\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.368422185266923e-19, \"text\": \"Mason, Ohio\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lindner_Family_Tennis_Center\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lindner_Family_Tennis_Center\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sabalenka, the world's third-ranked women's singles player, said after a French Open quarterfinal defeat two weeks ago that she had been very sick with a stomach bug the few days leading into the match.\", \"from\": 970, \"to\": 1172, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was the worst experience I had in my life on court,\\\" Sabalenka said Monday,according to the WTA.\", \"from\": 1174, \"to\": 1274, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1270, \"end\": 1273, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_Tennis_Association\", \"score\": 0.9946642487375048, \"rank\": 0.005317780280739562, \"text\": \"WTA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_Tennis_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_Tennis_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have played while being ill, I have played with injuries, but when you have a stomach bug and you do not have any energy to play and you are in the quarterfinal of a Grand Slam, that was really terrible experience.\", \"from\": 1275, \"to\": 1492, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But it is how it is.\", \"from\": 1493, \"to\": 1513, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think my body was just asking for some rest.\", \"from\": 1515, \"to\": 1562, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I managed to find a couple of days to chill and recover after the tough months.\\\"\", \"from\": 1563, \"to\": 1643, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She is scheduled to play at a grass-court tournament this week in Berlin, her first event since the French Open.\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1757, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1711, \"end\": 1717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\", \"score\": 0.9989029726933057, \"rank\": 0.0010815352934467877, \"text\": \"Berlin\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The grass season runs through Wimbledon, which ends in mid-July.\", \"from\": 1759, \"to\": 1823, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1789, \"end\": 1798, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Wimbledon_Championships\", \"score\": 0.9998095034528311, \"rank\": 0.00018852755863538615, \"text\": \"Wimbledon\", \"types\": [\"Q500834\", \"Q1656682\", \"Q13219666\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Wimbledon_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Wimbledon_Championships\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then the tours shift to primarily hard-court tournaments through the U.S. Open in early September.\", \"from\": 1824, \"to\": 1922, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics, which will be played on the same French Open clay at Roland Garros, are between Wimbledon and the U.S. Open.\", \"from\": 1924, \"to\": 2046, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For players who do take part in the Olympics, that can mean going from clay to grass back to clay and then 